Operating Executives & Advisors









 










Roger Fradin

Industry

Industrial
Transportation



Business Segment

Corporate Private Equity




Roger Fradin is an Operating Executive focused on the industrial and transportation sectors. He is based in New York.
Previously, Mr. Fradin served as Vice Chairman of Honeywell International from 2014 to 2017. Prior to this role, he served as President and CEO of Honeywell Automation and Controls Solutions for 10 years. Mr. Fradin joined Honeywell in 2000 when it acquired Pittway Corporation. During his 25-year tenure at Pittway, Mr. Fradin served in a variety of roles of increasing responsibility, ultimately serving as President and CEO of the Security and Fire Solutions segment.
Mr. Fradin received a B.S. and an M.B.A. from the Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania, where he also served as a member of the faculty.




































